16/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania will work on developing the OSCE's strategy against terrorism and human trafficking, as chairman of the organisation's Forum for Security Co-operation, according to a press release issued by the foreign ministry Wednesday (15 January).
During its four-month chairmanship, Tirana vows to focus on inter-state negotiations for weapons proliferation controls and disarmament, as well as on implementation of the Treaty of Conventional Weapons in Europe, the Treaty of Open Skies and the Measures for Building Trust and Security.
(ATA - 15/01/03)
